The paper discusses a language resource for document summarization, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The corpus was collected from arXiv, which is a digital library for computer science (cs.DL). The paper also mentions the use of document feature markup, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the distribution of types of information in summaries, which could be relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CY) researchers interested in identifying key information in large datasets.
